ns about hitchhiking as a rite of passage, and about the adult interventions that turned a subculture into a moral and social issue.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCounterculturezCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aHippieszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aHitchhikingzCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 0aYouth hostelszCanadaxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Post-Confederation (1867-).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311127363108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018z978311127598708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311141792940uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077483735440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774837354423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774837354/original  a978-3-11-127363-1  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-127598-7  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-141792-9  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles